 energy spectrum and we observe\nprominent multiplicity features related to an emergent symmetry predicted from\nthe quantum field theory. Building on these results we are able to address the\nsubtle crossover physics of the low-energy spectrum flowing from the chiral\nIsing fixed point to the Dirac fixed point, and analyze earlier flawed attempts\nto extract Fermi velocity renormalizations from the low-energy spectrum.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Jul 2019 16:50:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 15 Mar 2021 07:48:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-16"}
