 decomposition. In\nfull generality, for an additive category $\\mathsf A$ with (co)kernels and a\nprecovering class $\\mathsf L\\subset\\mathsf A$ closed under summands, an object\n$N\\in\\mathsf A$ has an $\\mathsf L$-cover if and only if a certain object\n$\\Psi(N)$ in an abelian category $\\mathsf B$ with enough projectives has a\nprojective cover. The $1$-tilting modules and objects arising from injective\nring epimorphisms of projective dimension $1$ form a class of examples which we\ndiscuss.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Jul 2019 00:57:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 6 Apr 2020 16:58:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 20 Oct 2020 17:57:33 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 8 Jan 2021 17:18:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-15"}
